{"title":"Teaching the Solow Model","link":"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/874395299/0/marginalrevolution~Teaching-the-Solow-Model.html","date":1711365354000,"content":"<p>The Solow model is a foundational model for understanding economic growth. Yet it’s typically not taught to principles students because it’s considered too difficult. In <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://marginalrevolution.com/our-textbook\">Modern Principles</a>, however, Tyler and I develop a super simple version of the model that is fun to teach and accessible to students of all levels. I’ll be talking about the Super Simple Solow model in a short webinar tomorrow (Tuesday March 26) at 1pm est. Register <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://go.macmillanlearning.com/register-240326-Solow-Model-for-Principles-of-Economics.html\">here</a>.</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"https://marginalrevolution.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/IMG_0116.jpeg\" width=\"603\" height=\"603\" srcset=\"https://marginalrevolution.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/IMG_0116.jpeg 720w, https://marginalrevolution.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/IMG_0116-300x300.jpeg 300w, https://marginalrevolution.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/IMG_0116-150x150.jpeg 150w\" /></p>\r\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://marginalrevolution.com/marginalrevolution/2024/03/teaching-the-solow-model-2.html\">Teaching the Solow Model</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://marginalrevolution.com\">Marginal REVOLUTION</a>.</p>\r\n<img height=\"1\" width=\"1\" src=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/i/874395299/0/marginalrevolution\" />\r\n<div><a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/28/874395299/marginalrevolution\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedblitz.com/i/fblike20.png\" /></a> <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/29/874395299/marginalrevolution,https%3a%2f%2fmarginalrevol